ENTRY            30249   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
SUBENT        30249001   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                 12         20
TITLE      Study of (n,alpha) reactions at thermal energies
AUTHOR     (J.Alam, M.I.Sehgal)
INSTITUTE  (3INDMUA)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,205,614,1973)
FACILITY   (REAC,3INDTRM)
INC-SOURCE (THCOL) Thermal neutron flux of the order of
            0.8 X 10E+08 n/cm2*sec
SAMPLE     Powder form, sandwiched between two thin pieces of
            cellotape. Sample purity better than 99.9%.
DETECTOR   End-window beta-counter with window thickness of
            1.5 mg/cm2.
METHOD     (ACTIV)
CORRECTION Corrections for the finite thickness of the target as
            well as window thickness of beta counter were taken
            into account in calculating the detection efficiency
STATUS     (TABLE,,J.Alam+,J,NP/A,205,614,1973) Table 1
HISTORY    (19730709C) FM.
           (20080423A) BIB section updated
           (20160623U) VS. DECAY-DATA corrected in 002.
           (20260407A) VT. Entry revised
ENDBIB              20
COMMON               1          3
EN
EV
    0.0253
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           27
SUBENT        30249002   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                  7         13
REACTION   ((72-HF-180(N,A)70-YB-177,,SIG)/
           (72-HF-180(N,G)72-HF-181,,SIG))
SAMPLE     Hafnium oxide powder
DECAY-DATA (70-YB-177-G,1.9HR,B)
           (70-YB-177-M,6.5SEC,B)
           (72-HF-181,43.D,B)
COMMENT    In present case the (n,alpha) cross section includes
            also the reaction 180Hf(n,a)177mYb
CORRECTION Decay curve of 177Yb corrected for background activity
            due to 181Hf.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
HISTORY    (20160623U) VS. DECAY-DATA corrected.
           (20260407A) VT. Original number expression restored.
ENDBIB              13
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 2          1
DATA       DATA-ERR
NO-DIM     NO-DIM
   38.5E-03    1.1E-03
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           21
SUBENT        30249003   20260407   20260528   20260528       3223
BIB                  5         10
REACTION   ((81-TL-203(N,A)79-AU-200-G,(M),SIG)/
           (81-TL-205(N,G)81-TL-206,,SIG))
DECAY-DATA (79-AU-200-G,48.MIN,B)
           (81-TL-206-G,4.3MIN,B)
SAMPLE     Thallous carbonate of 99.9% purity
COMMENT    Ratio given in data is only an upper limit because of
            the impossibility of separation of the activity due to
            the 203Tl(n,a)200Au reaction from that due to the
            205Tl(n,g) reaction
HISTORY    (20260407A) VT. Original number expression restored.
ENDBIB              10
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 1          1
DATA-MAX
NO-DIM
    2.5E-03
ENDDATA              3
ENDSUBENT           18
